  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>shallot[s] </strong>and <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Zest your <strong>lemon[s] </strong>and chop your <strong>dill </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Combine your <strong>beef mince </strong>in a large bowl with the <strong>lemon zest</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped shallot</strong>, <strong>garlic </strong>and <strong>dill </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong>, give everything a good mix up and shape into 3 <strong>meatballs </strong>per person</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606303686981-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606303686981-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606303686981-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606303686981-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606303686981-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat and boil a kettle</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> meatballs</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min on each side or until browned</p><p>Once the meatballs have browned, transfer them to a plate and set aside, these will finish cooking in the sauce later (reserve the pan!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1606303691434-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1606303691434-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1606303691434-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1606303691434-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1606303691434-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan (and any oil) to a medium-high heat and once hot, add the <strong>remaining chopped shallot</strong></p><p>Cook for 1-2 min or until softened</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>beef stock mix </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1606303701074-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
